<h3 id="step-2-bbg-to-internet">Step 2 BBG to Internet</h3>

<p>In “Control Panel”, enable Internet sharing. On my machine the device is called
“Apple USB Ethernet Adaptor” so you have to turn off the “Internet Sharing” service on the left, turn on the “Apple USB Ethernet Adaptor” and then turn on “Internet Sharing” to the the window below:</p>

<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2021/03/internetsharing.png">
  <img src="/assets/images/2021/03/internetsharing.png" alt="" />
  
    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>If you go back to the terminal on which you rang <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">screen</code>, you should be able to access the internet:</p>
<div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>debian@beaglebone:~<span class="nv">$ </span>ping <span class="nt">-c</span> 3 sydney.edu.au
